Description: I believe this is the very sought after Austin 786 model. It was advertised as the 786 model when I bought it but there are no readily identifiable markings. When searched on the net the images match up with the 786’s. It has excellent action, no fret buzz, a fast neck, sweet sounding pup’s and the frets are in great shape. The guitar looks beautiful, plays beautifully, is not a Les Paul but for the money can not be beat. It also has a set neck as opposed to a bolt on. It has cream binding along with gold hardware. Cosmetically is 8.5 to 9 out of 10 with a couple of light scratches on the back side that are difficult to see and more difficult to photograph and some light fading on some of the gold hardware. There is a little mark on the headstock you can see in picture number 8. Other than that just standard play wear. This is for someone that wants a quality instrument to play but is not stuck on a more famous brand name. Plays beautifully with excellent sustain. Welcome to make an offer. Please ask if you have any questions before placing a bid. I will try to get back with you ASAP. I have a 100% rating, check out my feedback. I only accept PayPal and ship only CONUS.
